# Direct production dependencies — source of truth.
#
# This file is the INPUT to pip-compile. Edit version constraints here,
# never in requirements.txt directly — requirements.txt is a generated
# lockfile and any manual edit to it will be silently overwritten the
# next time `make lock` (or `pip-compile requirements.in`) runs.
#
# Regenerate the lockfile with:
#   pip install pip-tools
#   pip-compile requirements.in --output-file requirements.txt --strip-extras
#
# Or simply: make lock   (see Makefile in repo root)
#
# dev/test-only packages (coverage, pytest, flower) live in
# requirements-dev.in / requirements-dev.txt instead.
